ratio_SM/PC: An increased SM to PC ratio enhances the  susceptibility of LDL to secretory sphingomyelinase, which leads to Cer generation and the formation of aggregated LDL exhibiting a high atherogenic potential. In contrast, the antiatherogenic potential of HDL (i.e., the cholesterol uptake capacity) may be enhanced by an enrichment of PC and SM. J Biol Chem. 1998 Jan 30;273(5):2738-46.
